cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the evaluation of word and concept embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses deep learning and various algorithms for learning embeddings, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses a knowledge graph to generate datasets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper analyzes the results and discusses the captured knowledge, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
